<section class="bio">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="bio__grid">
            <div class="bio__image-wrap reveal reveal--scale">
                <div class="bio__image">
                    <img src="/img/bogi-horvath-about.webp" alt="Boglarka Paczari-Horvath portrait — AI-Augmented Process Transformation Lead" width="560" height="640" loading="lazy">
                </div>
                <div class="bio__image-badge">
                    <p class="bio__image-badge-value">14+</p>
                    <p class="bio__image-badge-label">Years Tier-1</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bio__text">
                <div class="reveal">
                    <h2>My Journey — From Process Engineer to AI-Augmented Lead</h2>
                    <p>My professional path has always been driven by one question: <strong>"Is there a better way to do this?"</strong> Today, that question runs through an AI stack. Fourteen years ago, it ran through a stopwatch and a process map.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="reveal">
                    <p><strong>T-Systems (2011–2015) — the foundations.</strong> I started in IT service operations, managing service chains and learning that a process is only as good as the people who execute it. I led the KONE onboarding, cut client escalations by 30% via a cross-functional reporting framework, and earned my Six Sigma Greenbelt on a 10%-faster Order Management redesign. The discipline of ITIL became muscle memory.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="reveal">
                    <p><strong>British Telecom (2015–2022) — Lean Six Sigma at scale.</strong> Seven formative years. I redesigned the hung-line ITSM process and <strong>halved incident volume (-50%)</strong>. I automated internal ticket-quality checks and freed <strong>10 FTE / USD 100k+ annual run-rate</strong>. As Agile Deployment Lead, I drove <strong>21% adoption uplift</strong> on a PEGA workflow rollout — voluntary adoption with no mandate, won through stakeholder engagement. Change management at scale, with metrics on every move.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="reveal">
                    <p><strong>NTT Ltd. (2022–2024) — global standardisation.</strong> As Principal Business Operations Specialist, I harmonised the Opportunity-to-Cash value stream across 12 regional entities. I migrated billable change orders from legacy ERP to SAP S/4HANA, operationalised variable billing, and led the consolidation that retired three enterprise tools — <strong>EUR 500k+ in annual licence savings</strong>. Standardisation done correctly is what unlocks global scale.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="reveal">
                    <p><strong>InnovateIT Consulting (Sept 2024 – present) — my own vehicle.</strong> I founded InnovateIT Kft. as the B2B vehicle for single-engagement deep transformations. One client at a time, 12–18 month mandates, total focus. AI-augmented BPM advisory: process mining (Celonis, SAP Signavio), LLM-assisted SOP extraction, and EU AI Act governance framing.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bio__highlight reveal reveal--scale">
                    <h3>Current Focus — Functional Lead, S.W.I.F.T.</h3>
                    <p>I'm currently leading a 3–5 person team on E-form optimisation and API consolidation inside a Tier-1 financial-messaging transformation programme. <strong>50% API reduction projected.</strong> The breakthrough I'm proudest of: I built an AI-assisted documentation workflow on an offline GitHub Copilot deployment — running entirely inside the firm's tenant boundary — that <strong>cut technical-documentation cycle time by 60%</strong> and got engineering, product, and audit to sign off without rework.</p>
                    <p style="margin-top:var(--sp-3)"><a class="btn btn--secondary btn--sm" href="/blog/ai-documentation-swift/" data-cta-location="about_current_focus_case_study"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Read the case study</a></p>
                </div>

                <div class="reveal">
                    <h2>My Philosophy — Methodology First, Tools Second</h2>
                    <p>I don't believe in change for the sake of change. I believe in <strong>evidence-based transformation</strong>. Whether it's consolidating APIs, redesigning a workflow, or wiring up a Copilot pipeline, every decision has to be backed by data and aligned with the strategic goals of the organisation.</p>
                    <p>Lean Six Sigma + ITIL governance fluency translates directly into AI risk management — that's the differentiator versus AI-lab researchers parachuting into banks. <strong>In regulated firms, the compliant tool is the fast tool</strong> once audit is in the room. The faster cloud option that fails risk review is slower than the offline option that ships.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

